---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { pageSeo } from "../../seo/pages";
---

<BaseLayout
  title={pageSeo.contact.title}
  description={pageSeo.contact.description}
  keywords={pageSeo.contact.keywords}
>
  <section class="legal-page-section">
    <div class="container">
      <article>
        <p class="legal-kicker">Legal</p>
        <h1>Contact TADC Mind Games</h1>
        <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: June 30, 2026</p>

        <h2>Email</h2>
        <p>For all site inquiries, email wyong@tadcmindgames.org.</p>
        <p>Please use a clear subject line so your message can be reviewed more easily. Examples include Route Correction, Copyright Request, Broken Link, Build Update, or General Question.</p>

        <h2>What You Can Contact Us About</h2>
        <p>You can contact us about route corrections, outdated route information, build update notes, broken links, accessibility issues, copyright questions, attribution concerns, or general feedback about the site.</p>
        <p>Useful messages often include a specific page URL, the section title, what appears wrong or unclear, and what you believe should be changed. If you are reporting a gameplay route issue, include the route mood or page section involved, such as Caine pressure, Pomni panic, Kinger clues, <a href="/choices">choices</a>, <a href="/endings">endings</a>, or browser play.</p>

        <h2>Helpful Details to Include</h2>
        <p>If your message is about a specific page, include the page URL and a short description of the issue. If your message is about a route, ending, or choice, include the page name and the section that needs review. If your message is about copyright, include enough information for us to identify the material and understand your request.</p>
        <p>For copyright or attribution requests, include your name or organization, your relationship to the material, the exact URL where the material appears, and whether you are asking for removal, credit, replacement, or a correction.</p>

        <h2>Corrections and Route Notes</h2>
        <p>Because TADC Mind Games is still in development, route information can become outdated. If you notice that a choice, ending path, platform note, or troubleshooting suggestion no longer matches the current build, send the specific detail and how you tested it. The <a href="/updates">updates page</a> is the best place to compare current site notes before sending a correction.</p>

        <h2>Accessibility and Technical Issues</h2>
        <p>If a page is hard to read, a layout breaks on your device, a link does not work, or embedded play content does not load correctly, you can report the issue by email. Include your browser, device type, and the page URL when possible. For general site background, read the <a href="/legal/about-us">About Us page</a>.</p>

        <h2>Response Expectations</h2>
        <p>We try to review messages in a reasonable timeframe, but response times may vary. Sending a message does not guarantee that a page will be changed, but clear corrections and detailed issue reports are appreciated.</p>
        <p>We may not respond to every message, especially duplicate suggestions, vague requests, spam, or messages unrelated to the site. Legal and copyright requests should include enough detail to evaluate the request properly.</p>

        <h2>No Contact Form</h2>
        <p>This page does not include a contact form. Email is the only contact method listed for this site.</p>
        <p>Do not send passwords, private account details, payment information, or unnecessary personal data. This site does not require that information to answer normal route, gameplay, or legal inquiries.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page-section { position: relative; isolation: isolate; overflow: hidden; padding-block: clamp(46px, 5.4vw, 78px); background: radial-gradient(circle at 82% 8%, rgba(84, 216, 238, 0.12), transparent 22rem), radial-gradient(circle at 10% 0%, rgba(214, 77, 100, 0.12), transparent 18rem), linear-gradient(135deg, #09060c, #130817 52%, #09060c); }
  .legal-page-section::before { position: absolute; inset: 0; z-index: -1; content: ""; background: repeating-linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(248, 240, 231, 0.035) 0 1px, transparent 1px 80px), repeating-linear-gradient(0deg, rgba(248, 240, 231, 0.024) 0 1px, transparent 1px 44px); mask-image: linear-gradient(180deg, #000, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84), transparent 98%); pointer-events: none; }
  .legal-page-section .container { position: relative; }
  .legal-kicker, .legal-updated { color: var(--gold); font-size: 10px; font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .legal-page-section h1 { margin-top: 10px; font-size: clamp(30px, 4.2vw, 52px); line-height: 0.96; text-transform: uppercase; text-shadow: 0 0 22px rgba(214, 77, 100, 0.26), 0 2px 0 rgba(122, 36, 56, 0.44); }
  .legal-updated { margin-top: 14px; color: rgba(246, 184, 62, 0.76); }
  .legal-page-section h2 { margin-top: 30px; font-size: clamp(24px, 3vw, 34px); }
  .legal-page-section p { margin-top: 12px; color: rgba(248, 240, 231, 0.7); }
</style>
